name: Lane X
overview: Lane X (also spelled as Lane 'X') is a pinball game made using Olaf Lubeck's PCS (PinballConstruction Set in 1992) The actual person(s) responsible for this particular PCS game are not known, however it was released on PCS Club Disk #28, which was circulated by a group that made public domain PCS games in the late 1980s-early 1990s.
